---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service | The Princeton Journal">
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-10">

    <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500">
      Legal
    </p>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
      Terms of Service
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-6 text-gray-700">
      Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US')}
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-800">

      <p>
        These Terms of Service govern access to and use of The Princeton Journal website. By accessing or using this website, you agree to comply with these terms. If you do not agree, you should not use this website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Use of the Website
      </h2>

      <p>
        The Princeton Journal provides news, reporting, analysis, and public information. Content is provided for informational and journalistic purposes. You agree to use the website only for lawful purposes and in a manner that does not disrupt or harm the operation of the website or other users.
      </p>

      <p>
        You may not attempt to interfere with the website’s security, access restricted areas, scrape content in a manner that disrupts the service, or use the website for unlawful activity.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Accuracy and Editorial Standards
      </h2>

      <p>
        The Princeton Journal strives to ensure accuracy and fairness in all reporting. However, information may change over time and errors may occur. Content is provided on an “as available” basis without guarantees of completeness or accuracy.
      </p>

      <p>
        If an error is identified, corrections or clarifications may be issued within the relevant article or through updates to published material.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        User Submissions
      </h2>

      <p>
        Users may submit tips, documents, or information through the contact form or by email. By submitting material, you grant The Princeton Journal the right to review, verify, and use the information for reporting purposes.
      </p>

      <p>
        Submission of information does not guarantee publication. The Princeton Journal retains full editorial discretion over what information is investigated, reported, or published.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Intellectual Property
      </h2>

      <p>
        Unless otherwise noted, all articles, graphics, logos, and original content on this website are the property of The Princeton Journal and are protected by applicable copyright laws.
      </p>

      <p>
        Content may be quoted or referenced for commentary, research, or reporting provided proper attribution is given. Republishing full articles or large portions of content without permission is not permitted.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        External Links
      </h2>

      <p>
        Articles may include links to third party websites or documents for informational purposes. The Princeton Journal does not control and is not responsible for the content, accuracy, or practices of external websites.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Limitation of Liability
      </h2>

      <p>
        The Princeton Journal is not liable for damages or losses arising from the use of this website or reliance on information provided within it. Use of the website and its content is at your own discretion.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Changes to These Terms
      </h2>

      <p>
        These Terms of Service may be updated periodically to reflect changes in law, operations, or website functionality. Continued use of the website after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Contact
      </h2>

      <p>
        Questions regarding these terms may be directed to:
      </p>

      <p class="font-medium">
        theprincetonjournal@gmail.com
      </p>

    </div>

  </main>
</Layout>
